  "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #1662.\n\nTelegram `/solve`-family commands now use the configured yargs parser to identify the first positional GitHub URL, so commands like this work:\n\n```text\n/codex --model gpt-5.4-mini https://github.com/konard/p-vs-np/issues/476\n```\n\nThe fix also applies the same URL-position handling to `/hive`, while preserving reply-based URL extraction for commands such as `/solve --model opus`.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Added shared Telegram argument helpers for yargs parsing and URL-first normalization.\n- Updated `/solve` and `/hive` URL validation to read yargs positional output instead of assuming `args[0]` is the URL.\n- Kept malformed-flag validation before URL validation and after locked overrides are merged.\n- Added `tests/test-telegram-options-before-url.mjs` and included it in `npm test`.\n- Added a patch changeset.\n- Added the requested case study and captured issue/PR artifacts under `docs/case-studies/issue-1662/`.\n\n## Reproduction\n\nBefore the fix, `/codex --model gpt-5.4-mini <github-issue-url>` failed because `--model` was validated as the first argument.\n\nAfter the fix, yargs identifies the issue URL as the command positional argument and the bot normalizes the internal execution args back to URL-first form.\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\nnode tests/test-telegram-options-before-url.mjs\nnode tests/test-malformed-flags.mjs\nnpm run lint\nnpm test\n```\n\n## Evidence\n\nIssue screenshot captured in the case study:\n\n![Issue 1662 Telegram screenshot](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/blob/issue-1662-f172a7412294/docs/case-studies/issue-1662/screenshot-08ce9e7a.png?raw=true)\n",
